/wiki/Fukuoka: Fukuoka (福岡市, Fukuoka-shi, Japanese: [ɸɯ̥kɯꜜoka]) is the capital city of Fukuoka Prefecture, situated on the northern shore of the Japanese island Kyushu. It is the most populous city on the island, followed by Kitakyushu. It is the largest city and metropolitan area west of Keihanshin. The city was designated on April 1, 1972, by government ordinance. Greater Fukuoka, with a population of 2.5 million people (2005 census), is part of the heavily industrialized Fukuoka–Kitakyushu zone.
/wiki/Y%C5%ABsentei_Park: Yūsentei Park (友泉亭公園, Yūsentei-kōen) is a park in Jōnan-ku, Fukuoka, Japan. It was originally built in the mid-Edo period (1754) for Kuroda Tsugutaka, the 6th domain head of the Kuroda clan. It was named Yūsentei after a later lord's tanka poetry.
/wiki/Kurume,_Fukuoka: Kurume (久留米市, Kurume-shi) is a city in Fukuoka Prefecture, Japan.
/wiki/Asakura,_Fukuoka: Asakura (朝倉市, Asakura-shi) is a city located in south central Fukuoka Prefecture, Japan, on Kyūshū Island.
/wiki/Itoshima,_Fukuoka: Itoshima (糸島市, Itoshima-shi) is a city located in western Fukuoka Prefecture, Japan.
/wiki/Yame,_Fukuoka: Yame (八女市, Yame-shi) is a city located in Fukuoka Prefecture, Japan. The city was founded on April 1, 1954.
/wiki/List_of_Places_of_Scenic_Beauty_of: This list is of the Places of Scenic Beauty of Japan located within the Prefecture of Fukuoka.
